282.Title: 2004-Agreement questions with GWU Marines Army
282.mvDocSetName: Agreement questions with GWU Marines Army
282.DocumentSetDescription: Hello - we have multiple questions regarding some agreements. First, we have an agreement with GWU who provides our paramedic training. They want to update their partnership agreement with us. Our agreement with them went through DMF, but this agreement has to do with insurance coverage. Attached is the original and their requested update. The second question is about whether an agreement is needed between us an the Marine Corps and Army for special events support. They are charged our special events rates per our fee resolution, but last year provide the option to add in bonus money to encourage support. We also have a question if we can be a pass through agency for others to work these events. For example, we ask Fairfax to staff the event with us, can we then charge Marines for Fairfax and then send that money back to Fairfax...Thank you! Megan

457.FileLeafRef: 2324-Arlington Addiction Recover Initiaive - Sustance Use Release Form
457.Title: 2324-Arlington Addiction Recover Initiaive - Sustance Use Release Form
457.mvDocSetName: Suboxone Treatment Information Sharing Release Form
457.DocumentSetDescription: This is a required document for patients who we treat for opioid addiction in the field to sign permission for the ACFD Mobile Integrated Health Qualified Healthcare Provider to share protected health information with addiction recovery resources. It is an important part of closing the circle for addiction recovery and allows the process to continue for the patient. The patient does not have to sign to be treated by us, but it closes the circle if they do and increases the success of recovery overall. We would like the County attorney to review and approve this consent form for use. Our addiction recovery partners in the County have reviewed and agree.
